The result is a focal plane more than three times flatter than a standard Schmidt-Cassegrain telescope and dramatically flatter than other competing coma-free designs, guaranteeing sharp stars across today's largest CCD sensors.

about_this_item: Leica Summilux-M 50mm f/1.4 ASPH. Lens (2023) - A Contemporary Classic: This lens represents a modern reimagining of the beloved 50mm focal length, with a redesigned housing and updated optics.

High-Speed Performance and Versatility: As a part of the Summilux class, it excels in low-light conditions and offers exceptional control over depth of field, making it a versatile tool for photographers.

Enhanced Optical Design: The lens is optimized for use with newer high-resolution sensors, resulting in improved sharpness, resolution, and contrast. An aspherical element minimizes aberrations and distortion for precise image rendering.

Smooth Bokeh and Compact Design: The lens features an innovative 11-blade diaphragm for smoother bokeh, and its compact design (2.3 x 2.3 inches, weighing just under 12 ounces) makes it a portable choice for photographers.

Live View Compatibility and Integrated Hood: With a reduced minimum focusing distance of 1.5 feet, it's ideal for cameras with live view capabilities. The integrated retractable lens hood eliminates the need for an additional hood, enhancing convenience for photographers on the go.
details.product_descriptions: Unveiling the Leica Summilux-M 50mm f/1.4 ASPH. Lens of 2023 - a modern interpretation of this revered focal length. With a redesigned housing and updated optics, this lens breathes new life into the beloved 50mm f/1.4. Widely recognized as one of the most adaptable lenses, the enhanced 50mm f/1.4 now presents an improved minimum focusing distance of 1.5 feet, an innovative 11-blade diaphragm for smoother bokeh, and a refreshed lens body that harmonizes with the sleek and lightweight design of the Summilux-M 35mm. It also features a built-in, retractable lens hood. As part of the distinguished Summilux class, it delivers impressive high-speed performance, making it suitable for low-light conditions and providing superior control over depth of field. The updated optical design is finely tuned to complement the latest high-resolution sensors, resulting in heightened sharpness, resolution, and contrast. An aspherical element minimizes spherical aberrations and distortion, ensuring precise image reproduction. Furthermore, the new 11-blade diaphragm produces a visually pleasing, rounded bokeh when shooting at intermediate apertures. The lens boasts an M-Mount design, aligning with the aesthetic updates seen in other modern Summilux-M lenses, such as the 35mm f/1.4. The minimum focusing distance has been reduced from 2.3 feet to 1.5 feet, making it a perfect match for cameras with live view capabilities or when using the Visoflex or Leica FOTOS app. While rangefinder focusing is limited to 2.3 feet, live view focusing can be employed between 2.3 feet and 1.5 feet. The integrated retractable lens hood eliminates the necessity for an additional hood, streamlining portability and convenience. Compact in design, it measures 2.3 x 2.3 inches and weighs just under 12 ounces. The conventional M bayonet lens mount includes 6-bit encoding, ensuring compatibility with a range of M-mount rangefinder cameras.

about_this_item: 【2 Light Kit Including Accessories】The Dracast DRKP1000B2K LED Video Light Kit includes x2 Dracast Kala Plus Series LED1000 Bicolor LED video lights, each with diffusion panel, mounting yoke and AC power adapter. The lighting kit also includes x2 light stands, x2 Kala Plus barndoors, x2 carry cases, and an injection molded hard plastic travel case with wheels and telescoping handle.

【Remote Control with the Dracast Kala Plus App】Control one or multiple lights simultaneously from over 100 feet using the Dracast Kala Plus App for iOS and Android. Assign groups for multi-light control. Control color temperature and adjust dimming from 0% - 100% entirely within the app.

【Bi-Color Adjustable Color Temperature】Easily match ambient lighting with 2800K - 6500K adjustable CCT. 96+ CRI and TLCI for excellent color rendition across the entire CCT range. Excellent for interview lighting, portrait lighting, and on-location lighting where matching existing light sources is essential.

【DMX512 Input and Output】 Dracast Kala Plus comes ready for studio installation with DMX512 input and output ports with three pin connectors. Address your Kala Plus lights quickly and easily using on the LCD digital display panel.
【0%  100% Dimming】 Control your lights completely with flicker-free dimming from 0% output to 100% output. Dim via manual control, DMX control, or using the Dracast Kala Plus app.

【AC / DC Power Options】Plug the Kala Plus Series panel into the wall using the included AC / DC power adapter or take your light on location with battery power. Dracast Kala Plus Series lights include a v-mount battery plate compatible with v-mount style batteries (sold separately). Light can operate for several hours on a full battery charge

【Dracast Build Quality and Included Accessories】Built with an anodized aluminum metal housing for excellent durability. Quick and easy manual control with the Kala Plus Series advanced digital user interface. Includes mounting yoke with 5/8' baby pin adapter. Includes pre-installed diffusion filter for soft, even lighting and four-way barn doors for excellent light output control. Individual soft carrying case is included for storage and transport.
